    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm trying to plan a trip from Heathrow to Edinburgh and I'm a bit worried about the tight connections. If I take the Heathrow Express to Paddington and then need to catch an LNER train north, how much buffer time should I realistically leave for the transfer? Also, I'll need to catch a local bus once I get to Edinburgh, so I want to make sure the whole itinerary is solid.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A good, solid transfer time for a trip like that, especially when you're dealing with the chaos of train schedules, is about a full 45 minutes to an hour. Give yourself that buffer, because you never know when a particular train will be delayed. It's better to have extra time than to be stuck waiting for a train that's been held up by some slow-moving piece of cargo or, worse, a grumpy local. Remember, even the smoothest journey has little snags, and those little snags are usually where the real trouble starts.",
