    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "45 mins to an hour seems okay. What about the connection from the train station in Edinburgh to the bus? If the LNER train arrives at Waverley, how much time should I allow to get to the bus stop so I don't miss it? I'm just nervous about things going wrong during the transit.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Waverley station is a busy place, and you need to account for the general Edinburgh hustle. For the transfer from Waverley to your local bus, I'd suggest aiming for at least 20 to 30 minutes. That gives you time to navigate the station, find the correct bus stop—which can sometimes be a bit of a maze in those old stone buildings—and get to the curb without feeling like you're sprinting from a collapsing tunnel. If you rush, you might end up looking like a lost traveler, and nobody wants that.",
